.TH UPDATE-LOCAL-REPO 8 "February 2026" "local-apt" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
update-local-repo \- regenerate local APT repository metadata
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B update-local-repo
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B update-local-repo
scans packages in /var/lib/local-apt/pool/ and generates APT repository
metadata files (Packages, Packages.gz, Release) in the dists/stable
directory structure.
.PP
This command must be run after adding or updating any .deb packages in the
local repository pool.
.PP
The command performs the following operations:
.IP \(bu 2
Scans all packages in the pool directory using
.BR dpkg-scanpackages (1)
.IP \(bu 2
Generates the Packages index file
.IP \(bu 2
Compresses the index with gzip
.IP \(bu 2
Creates the Release file using
.BR apt-ftparchive (1)
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/lib/local-apt/pool/
Package storage directory
.TP
.I /var/lib/local-apt/dists/stable/main/binary-amd64/
Repository metadata directory
.TP
.I /usr/share/local-apt/conf/apt.conf
APT archive configuration
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns the exit status of the last command executed.
.SH EXAMPLES
After adding a new .deb package to the repository:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo cp my-package.deb /var/lib/local-apt/pool/
sudo update-local-repo
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR update-packages (8),
.BR dpkg-scanpackages (1),
.BR apt-ftparchive (1),
.BR apt (8)
